<br>
It's biased. It's brainwashing ignorant mages... they didn't know about most of the times in the 'history' of the class, but now they know a little about them. That's good. The problem with it is ylaine only told what she wanted people to know &gt;&lt; I can't blame her at all for making the post this way. The idea of posting is to encourage people toward a certain opinion. But now I know people are gonna be quoting this post all over in 'mage is supposed to be dmg class!' posts, which is bad for the community. It's just not good to have people spreading information 2nd hand, that's like rumors, and we know how they get out of hand.<br>
<br>
What I ask is: that no mage take ylaine history as if it were full and unbiased. Just know that it does omit some stuff here and there, such as what silverblade pointed out. If you wanna think mages should be a dmg class etc etc fine. Ylaine's post is mostly facts, and the facts are easily discernable from the author's opinions. All I'm asking is for you, the reader, to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  acknowledge the fact that this post is not an unbiased history,</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> but is a persuasive argument meant to prove her point. Also for this reason I disagree with it being moved to the library. The library is for factual posts and such, ylaine's history is, again, persuasive argument.<br>
<br>
So anyway, maybe I'll put together an altogether different history of a mage. I've been playing since EQ went gold, but haven't been mage all along, but since before kunark. Reason I post this reply is because too many mages replied with 'oh now i understand' and 'great job' type of things. This history doesn't look the same as the history I remember &gt;&lt; so i doth protest<br>
<br>
